      "raw_text": "OLYMPIA. Nov. 30.-Three rail\nway brakemen, until recently EN-\nployed on trains No SO and No. 20\nthe local freights operated on the\nOlympia branch out of Tacoma\nwere in Olympia today to enter a\ncomplaint with the railroad com.\nmission that they had been dis\ncharged by the Northern Pacific\nfor refusing to disobey the state\nlaw limiting the hours of railway\ntrainmen to Is consecutive hours\nThe company's record is said to\nshow INSTRUMENTATION as the ground\nfor dismissal. Theh trainmen found\nnone of the members of the rail.\nroad commission in the city, but\non their return they will probably\ntake the matter up."
    }
